FIRST DISTRICT.

No. 46-2160.Samuel Sheller, etc., v. Britton E. CluckOpinion filed Nov. 25, 1885.A suit in assumpsit to recover the amount of a promissory note for $500 and interest, purporting to have been executed by the defendants to the plaintiff. No complaint is made of any of the rulings of the court at the trial, nor of any of the instructions given to the jury. The court being of opinion that the verdict was not contrary to the preponderance of the evidence the judgment is affirmed.Attorneys for appellant, Mr. James Siiaw, Mr. E. E. Dutciier and Mr. Nelson Fletcher ;for appellee, Mr. J. M. Hunter.

Opinion by Bailey, P. J. Judge below, John Y. Eustace.
